casebody.data:
Winchester et al., Appellants, v. Pike et al., Appellees.

[Cite as Winchester v. Pike (1986), 22 Ohio St. 3d 227.]

(No. 85-1165 Decided March 12, 1986.) Webb & DiFabio and John J. Luce, for appellants. Baker, Hackenberg, Haskell & Collins Co., L.P.A., and I. James Hackenberg, for appellees.

This cause on appeal from the court of appeals (case No. 10-196) is reversed on authority of Anson v. Tyree (1986), 22 Ohio St. 3d 223, decided this date.

Celebrezze, C.J., Locher, Holmes, C. Brown, Douglas and Wright, JJ., concur. Sweeney, J., not participating.
